        <div class="abstract">
          <div class="name">
            <h1>
              Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves            </h1>
          </div>
          <div class="describe">
            <p><span style="font-size: 18px;">Customizable carbon fiber heating pads for gloves offer rapid, uniform heating and energy efficiency. With options for voltage, size, and power, they are perfect for electric heating gloves, outdoor sports, and therapeutic uses. Safe, durable, and suitable for various applications.</span></p>          </div>
          <div class="consult">
            <a href="javascript:get_a_quote(58);">Inquire Now</a>
                      </div>
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
        <div class="productdetailtab">
          <ul class="productdetailtabli">
            <li class="current">Product Details</li>
                                              </ul>
          <div class="productdetailtabbox">
            <div class="productdetailtabcon show">
                <p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">The <strong data-start="171" data-end="210">Carbon Fiber <a href='../silicone-heating-plate/silicone-heating-pad/index.html'  target="_blank">Heating Pad</a> for <a href='../electric-heated-gloves/heated-gloves/index.html'  target="_blank">Gloves</a></strong> is a flexible heating element that uses carbon fiber as the heating material. It offers advantages such as rapid heating, uniform heating, high energy efficiency, softness, and folding resistance. It is widely used in <strong data-start="429" data-end="456">electric heating gloves</strong>, <strong data-start="458" data-end="472">ski gloves</strong>, <strong data-start="474" data-end="501">electric vehicle gloves</strong>, <strong data-start="503" data-end="532">outdoor heating equipment</strong>, and other fields to meet various environmental and user needs.</span></p><p style="text-align: center;"><img src="../upload/image/20250424/1745465295164147.jpg" width="300" height="300" border="0" vspace="0" alt="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves" title="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves"/><img src="../upload/image/20250424/1745465296986272.jpg" width="300" height="300" border="0" vspace="0" alt="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves" title="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves"/></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><strong><span style="font-size: 20px;">Product Advantages</span></strong></p><ol data-start="626" data-end="2270"><li><p data-start="629" data-end="952" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="629" data-end="673">Rapid Heating and High Energy Efficiency</strong></span></p><p data-start="629" data-end="952" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="629" data-end="673"></strong>Using high-purity carbon fiber as the heating material, the <strong data-start="737" data-end="765">carbon fiber heating pad</strong> can heat up quickly within <strong data-start="793" data-end="809">5-10 seconds</strong> after power is turned on. It has high heat conversion efficiency, significantly reducing energy consumption and improving heating performance.</span></p></li><li><p data-start="957" data-end="1243" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="957" data-end="996">Soft, Thin, and Strong Adaptability</strong></span></p><p data-start="957" data-end="1243" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="957" data-end="996"></strong>The thickness of the heating pad is as low as approximately <strong data-start="1060" data-end="1069">0.4mm</strong>, soft and bendable, making it easy to sew or embed in various glove structures, ensuring wearing comfort and <strong data-start="1179" data-end="1223">adaptability for electric heating gloves</strong> of various designs.</span></p></li><li><p data-start="1248" data-end="1491" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1248" data-end="1289">Uniform Heating, Comfortable and Safe</strong></span></p><p data-start="1248" data-end="1491" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1248" data-end="1289"></strong>The heating wire is scientifically arranged to prevent local overheating, ensuring uniform heating. It works with a low-voltage DC power supply (<strong data-start="1438" data-end="1461">3.7V, 5V, 7.4V, 12V</strong>), ensuring safety during use.</span></p></li><li><p data-start="1496" data-end="1802" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1496" data-end="1543">Support Customization, Flexible and Diverse</strong></span></p><p data-start="1496" data-end="1802" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1496" data-end="1543"></strong><strong data-start="1547" data-end="1584">Carbon fiber glove heating sheets</strong> can be customized for size, power, voltage, interface type, appearance, and packaging form according to customer needs, meeting the diversified demands of brands, especially for <strong data-start="1763" data-end="1801">customized electric heating gloves</strong>.</span></p></li><li><p data-start="1807" data-end="2050" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1807" data-end="1850">Long Service Life, Reliable and Durable</strong></span></p><p data-start="1807" data-end="2050" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="1807" data-end="1850"></strong>Carbon fiber offers excellent oxidation resistance and fatigue resistance. It has been tested to withstand more than <strong data-start="1971" data-end="1986">3,000 bends</strong> without damage, making it suitable for long-term, frequent use.</span></p></li><li><p data-start="2055" data-end="2270" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="2055" data-end="2101">Complete Certifications, Quality Assurance</strong></span></p><p data-start="2055" data-end="2270" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="2055" data-end="2101"></strong>The product can pass <strong data-start="2126" data-end="2147">CE, RoHS, FCC, UL</strong>, and other certifications, and we provide complete test reports to help customers smoothly enter the international market.</span></p></li></ol><p data-start="2055" data-end="2270" class=""><br/></p><p><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="2276" data-end="2297"></strong></span></p><p style="text-align: center;"><img src="../upload/image/20250424/1745465358513308.jpg" width="300" height="300" border="0" vspace="0" alt="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves" title="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves"/><img src="../upload/image/20250424/1745465358803954.jpg" width="300" height="300" border="0" vspace="0" alt="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves" title="Carbon Fiber Heating Pad for Gloves"/></p><h2><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="102" data-end="139">Product Parameters</strong></span></h2><div class="group pointer-events-none relative flex justify-center *:pointer-events-auto"><div class="tableContainer horzScrollShadows relative"><table class="min-w-full" data-start="141" data-end="1136" width="1481"><thead data-start="141" data-end="223"><tr data-start="141" data-end="223" class="firstRow"><th data-start="141" data-end="164" style="border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="143" data-end="151">Item</strong></span></th><th data-start="164" data-end="223" style="border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="166" data-end="191">Parameter Description</strong></span></th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="307" data-end="1136"><tr data-start="307" data-end="390"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="307" data-end="331" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="309" data-end="329">Heating Material</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="331" data-end="390" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">High-purity carbon fiber filament</span></td></tr><tr data-start="391" data-end="478"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="391" data-end="415" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="393" data-end="410">Voltage Range</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)] min-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)/3)]" data-start="415" data-end="478" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">3.7V / 5V / 7.4V / 12V (customizable based on requirements)</span></td></tr><tr data-start="479" data-end="562"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="479" data-end="503" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="481" data-end="496">Power Range</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="503" data-end="562" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">2W ~ 15W (customizable)</span></td></tr><tr data-start="563" data-end="646"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="563" data-end="587" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="565" data-end="582">Standard Size</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)] min-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)/3)]" data-start="587" data-end="646" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">80×50mm, 100×60mm, etc. (customizable in any shape)</span></td></tr><tr data-start="647" data-end="730"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="647" data-end="671" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="649" data-end="662">Thickness</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)] min-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)/3)]" data-start="671" data-end="730" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Approximately 0.4~1mm (depending on structure design)</span></td></tr><tr data-start="731" data-end="826"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="731" data-end="755" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="733" data-end="754">Connection Method</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)] min-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)/3)]" data-start="755" data-end="826" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Plug wire, welded wire, USB interface, DC head, etc. (customizable)</span></td></tr><tr data-start="827" data-end="917"><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)]" data-start="827" data-end="851" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="372" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="829" data-end="850">Temperature Range</strong></span></td><td class="max-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)*2/3)] min-w-[calc(var(--thread-content-max-width)/3)]" data-start="851" data-end="917" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(221, 221, 221);" width="1108" align="center" valign="middle"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Room temperature ~ 65℃ (adjustable based on voltage and power)</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><h3 data-start="2272" data-end="2297" class=""><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="2276" data-end="2297">Working Principle</strong></span></h3><p data-start="2299" data-end="3137" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;">The working principle of the <strong data-start="2328" data-end="2362">carbon fiber glove heating pad</strong> is based on the conductive heating properties of carbon fiber. When current passes through the carbon fiber filament, the carbon fiber generates heat due to its resistance and releases the heat energy. The heating process is stable and controllable, without producing open flames or electromagnetic interference. It works with a low-voltage DC power supply and can achieve an ideal heating effect within the range of <strong data-start="2780" data-end="2792">3.7V~12V</strong>, which is highly effective in quickly warming the hands and enhancing the warmth experience. Additionally, it can be paired with a temperature control module to achieve constant temperature adjustments, segmented temperature control, intelligent on/off, and other features to meet the temperature requirements of various environments and users.</span></p><p data-start="2299" data-end="3137" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><h3 data-start="3139" data-end="3165" class=""><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="3143" data-end="3165">Application Fields</strong></span></h3><p data-start="3167" data-end="3348" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3167" data-end="3202">Carbon fiber glove heating pads</strong> are widely used in wearable devices that require local heating, close-fitting warmth, and low-voltage safety. They are particularly suitable for:</span></p><ol data-start="3349" data-end="3917"><li><p data-start="3352" data-end="3457" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3352" data-end="3379">Electric heating gloves</strong> (electric bike gloves, motorcycle gloves, ski gloves, cold-proof work gloves)</span></p></li><li><p data-start="3461" data-end="3557" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3461" data-end="3489">Outdoor sports equipment</strong> (heating gloves for mountaineering, skiing, fishing, cycling, etc.)</span></p></li><li><p data-start="3561" data-end="3663" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3561" data-end="3600">Physiotherapy/rehabilitation gloves</strong> (relieve rheumatism, arthritis, and promote blood circulation)</span></p></li><li><p data-start="3667" data-end="3756" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3667" data-end="3704">Touch-screen smart heating gloves</strong> (touchscreen gloves combined with heating function)</span></p></li><li><p data-start="3760" data-end="3825" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3760" data-end="3825">Military, police, security, and logistics cold-proof supplies</strong></span></p></li><li><p data-start="3829" data-end="3917" class=""><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3829" data-end="3862">Customized brand winter gifts</strong> (heating gloves, heating socks, heating clothes, etc.)</span></p></li></ol><p data-start="3829" data-end="3917" class=""><br/></p><p><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="3923" data-end="3930"><br/></strong></span></p><h3 data-start="3919" data-end="3930" class=""><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong data-start="3923" data-end="3930">FAQ</strong></span></h3><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="3935" data-end="4006">1.What voltages are the carbon fiber glove heating pads suitable for?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">The <strong data-start="4014" data-end="4051">carbon fiber glove heating sheets</strong> we provide support various voltage options, including <strong data-start="4106" data-end="4129">3.7V, 5V, 7.4V, 12V</strong>, and can be customized according to customer needs to adapt to different devices and power supply methods.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="4241" data-end="4296">2.What is the working temperature of the heating pad?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">The working temperature of the <strong data-start="4331" data-end="4360">carbon fiber glove heater</strong> is typically between <strong data-start="4382" data-end="4397">30℃ and 65℃</strong>, depending on voltage, power, and usage environment. You can choose the appropriate temperature control design to ensure a balanced and comfortable temperature.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="4563" data-end="4619">3.Can I customize the size of the carbon fiber heater?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Yes, our <strong data-start="4632" data-end="4661">carbon fiber glove heater</strong> supports custom sizing, shapes, and power. We can tailor the size, shape, heating range, and interface type based on your specific needs to ensure a perfect fit for your product design.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="4852" data-end="4914">4.What is the service life of the carbon fiber glove heater?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">The <strong data-start="4922" data-end="4951">carbon fiber glove heater</strong> has a long service life and can withstand over <strong data-start="4999" data-end="5013">3000 bends</strong> without affecting performance. Under normal usage, the service life can extend to <strong data-start="5096" data-end="5109">5-7 years</strong>.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="5115" data-end="5157">5.Is the carbon fiber glove heater safe?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Yes, the <strong data-start="5170" data-end="5198">carbon fiber heating pad</strong> uses a low-voltage DC power supply (<strong data-start="5235" data-end="5258">3.7V, 5V, 7.4V, 12V</strong>) and is very safe. It heats evenly without producing open flames or electromagnetic radiation. It is reliable for use and meets <strong data-start="5387" data-end="5421">international safety standards</strong>. We also provide <strong data-start="5439" data-end="5445">CE</strong>, <strong data-start="5447" data-end="5455">RoHS</strong>, and other certifications to ensure safety.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="5504" data-end="5561">6.Can you make a custom design based on my glove style?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Absolutely! We support <strong data-start="5588" data-end="5608">drawing proofing</strong>, sample customization, and can assist with structural matching and design suggestions.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="5700" data-end="5768">7.Is there a ready-made mold for the product?</strong></span><strong data-start="5700" data-end="5768" style="font-size: 18px;">Is there a mold fee?</strong></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Some popular specifications already have molds available. If a custom mold is needed, we will evaluate the cost and provide a transparent quotation.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong data-start="5925" data-end="5984">8.Is the product heated evenly? Will it overheat locally?</strong></span></p><p style="line-height: 1.75em;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">We use a <strong data-start="5997" data-end="6041">uniformly arranged carbon fiber filament</strong> structure to effectively prevent local overheating, ensuring even and safe heating throughout the product.</span></p><p><br/></p>            </div>
